The paper deals with improving the speed of distributed computation in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of network coding is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses lower bounds and algorithms, which are topics that fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on dynamic networks and adaptivity suggests that it could also be classified under distributed computing (cs.DC) and self-organizing systems (cs.SI).
